<w type="h2">Alignment</w>
<w type="p">Spinners in LC Design are built with [color=#bd4147][bgcolor=#fdf4f4] px [/bgcolor][/color], [color=#bd4147][bgcolor=#fdf4f4] currentColor [/bgcolor][/color], and [color=#bd4147][bgcolor=#fdf4f4] display: inline-block [/bgcolor][/color]. This means they can easily be resized, recolored, and quickly aligned.</w>
<w type="h3">Margin</w>
<w type="p">Use margin utilities like .m-5 for easy spacing.</w>

<w class="demo-box margin-spinners-demo">
  <w class="demo-preview-box"><spinner class="m-5" /></w>
  <w type="code-block" class="code-block">[color=#062873][b]&lt;spinner[/color][/b] [color=#4070a0]class=[/color][color=#a31515]&quot;m-5&quot;[/color] [color=#062873][b]/&gt;[/color][/b]</w>
</w>
<w type="h3">Placement</w>
<w type="p">Use flexbox utilities, float utilities to place spinners exactly where you need them in any situation.</w>
<w type="h4">Flex</w>

<w class="demo-box flex-spinners-demo">
  <w class="demo-preview-box"><w class="d-flex justify-content-center">
  <spinner />
</w></w>
  <w type="code-block" class="code-block">[color=#062873][b]&lt;w[/color][/b] [color=#4070a0]class=[/color][color=#a31515]&quot;d-flex justify-content-center&quot;[/color][color=#062873][b]&gt;[/color][/b]
  [color=#062873][b]&lt;spinner[/color][/b] [color=#062873][b]/&gt;[/color][/b]
[color=#062873][b]&lt;/w&gt;[/color][/b]</w>
</w>
<w type="h2">Size</w>
<w type="p">Set [color=#bd4147][bgcolor=#fdf4f4] size="small" [/bgcolor][/color] attribute to make a smaller spinner.</w>

<w class="demo-box size-spinners-demo">
